==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:H. L. Mencken|H. L. Mencken]] from ''[[ekdysis]]'' (on the model of ''[[enthusiast]]'' etc.).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ɛkˈdɪzɪæst/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An [[erotic]] [[dancer]] who removes their [[clothes]] as a form of [[entertainment]].
#*'''1973''': I had never seen an '''ecdysiast''' before; toward the end she was wearing nothing but seven beads, four of them sweat. — Kyril Bonfiglioli, ''Don't Point That Thing at Me'' (Penguin 2001, p. 79)

===Synonyms===
* [[stripper]]
* [[exotic dancer]]

